article.headline: Ohio 73, Shippensburg 57
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Eric Hall and Jesse Becker scored 19 points apiece to lead South Dakota to a its 10th straight opening-day win, a 78-73 overtime victory over Shippensburg Friday. The Coyortes trailed by 12 in the second half before rallying. Dustin Little made a long 3-pointer to send the game to overtime, where USD outscored the Red Raiders 13-8. USD was 11-for-23 from 3-point range. The Coyotes shot 47 percent from the field. Little had 17 points and Dyland Grimsley 13 for USD. Shippensburg was led by Chuck Davis with 22 points. Greg Wojdowski had 15 points and Todd Johnson 14.
